This paper discusses a personal data market and proposes a pricing mechanism that balances privacy and money. The paper involves topics related to cybersecurity (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), social and information networks (cs.SI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses user preferences and conducts an online survey, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY, followed by cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SI, and cs.HC.
